MetalSoft manages not just servers, but also storage and This unlocks capabilities previously only possible on virtualized infrastructures, such as instant hardware replacement, snapshots, and hardware-provided telemetry, automatic firmware updates, health checks, Hierarchical control plane Whether it is a single server, or a million servers spread across tens of thousands of datacenter locations, MetalSoft can fully manage them all under a single UI as well as through The mission of MetalSoft is to enable operators to manage all their datacenter equipment with , from initial deployment to MetalSoft’s core architecture consists of a single lightweight agent per datacenter (which is small enough to run on a switch) working in conjunction with a hierarchical control The entire control plane only requires two servers to manage multiple datacenters with thousands of servers and can expand horizontally as needed to manage larger Services In addition to the hardware devices, the building blocks of MetalSoft Infrastructure include a set of deeply integrated software applications frameworks as well, making it quite Kubernetes service MetalSoft’s unique L2 networking support enables the latency of communication to be reduced by as much as compared to the public cloud Kubernetes Database service MetalSoft also provides support for a number of SQL and NoSQL databases that operators can deliver as a service as well, including Cassandra, MySQL and Big data service MetalSoft also provides support for a number of data processing frameworks including Cloudera, MapR (now HP), and Blueprints and Infrastructure editor MetalSoft makes it easy to design reusable ‘blueprints’ using a UI to build a logical diagram of the This blueprint can then be The Ultimate Guide to Negotiating Your Medical Bills | Resolve Medical Bills | Medical Bill Negotiation resolve is Here is what we’re doing during the What We Do About Us The Guide Part 1: Understanding Your Medical Bills Part 2: Negotiating Your Medical Bills Part 3: Getting Help with Your Medical Bills Blog Contact Us Select Page Thanks! Click here to download your PDF copy of The Guide! Download the Guide as a PDF file Read this informative reference on your device at any We guarantee your email address is safe with Download PDF Proceed to download Part 2: Negotiating Your Medical Bills In Part 1: Understanding Your Medical Bills , we provided background on how dangerously medical costs have become, and walked through typical medical documents from hospitals and insurance providers to help you understand exactly what you’re being charged for — and Now we’ll dive into the process of negotiating your medical That process starts with gathering ALL of the right information, then recognizing problems that might be relevant to your specific Finally, we’ll guide you through what you can do to help reduce those There is no approach to appealing — and lowering — an exorbitant medical While there are some standards around terminology and paperwork, hospitals and insurance companies tend to phrase or present things differently, often causing confusion (which may, in fact, be the point). For example, what the hospital bill calls the “insurance adjustment” may be referred to as the “plan discount” on your insurance company’s Explanation of As we laid out in Part 1 of this guide, understanding those nuances is key to taking the next In order to start negotiating your hospital bill, you need to dig deeper into why you’ve been billed a certain In other words, what particular issue (or issues) can you identify, whether it seems like or an unexpected insurance denial? In this part, we’ll identify the possible issues with your bill, dividing them into 4 buckets — , Insurance Denial, Balance Billing, and Billing Errors — and providing detailed descriptions of each scenario and how to prepare for negotiating the (Note: these buckets may seem dense and overly We’re trying to provide as much information as possible, as clearly as possible, so read ) Finally, we’ll help you apply that knowledge to the actual We recommend following this process, which has led to significant bill reductions for our clients: Step 1: Gather the RIGHT Information (always more complex than it sounds) Step 2: Analyze, Understand, and Fix the Issue (less complex than it sounds) Step 3: Negotiate (requires patience, persistence, attention to detail, and a refusal to accept “no” for an answer) Step 1: Gather the RIGHT Information The first step to negotiating your hospital bill is to make sure you have in your possession — and that you understand — all of the relevant documents for your (For a refresher on how to understand your hospital bill and insurance Explanation of Benefits, reread our section in Part 1: Understanding Your Medical Bills .) These include: Hospital Bill Itemized Hospital Bill Explanation of Benefits (if you carry insurance) Hospital Bill Your hospital bill is typically sent to you in the It comes from the hospital and lists total charges along with any discounts offered, insurance company coverage, and what you as the patient Itemized Hospital Bill This is breakdown of ALL charges, line by This won’t be sent automatically you have to call the number on your hospital and ask specifically for the Itemized Hospital Bill . Hospitals aren’t inclined to provide this information, but they are required by law to do so if you Make sure to be clear and direct, and say something along the lines of “I would like an itemized ” The itemized bill should have a list of the charges and the associated “revenue code” (the internal code the hospital uses to determine their charge), the CPT or HCPCS code (used to identify what services were provided), and charges for each line Explanation of Benefits (EOB) If you have insurance, your insurance company should have sent this to If your insurance company has an online portal, it’s almost always posted Additionally, you can call your insurance company and ask them to send an EOB to If you don’t have insurance, don’t worry about this Note: If it feels frustrating and difficult to gather even these three simple documents, don’t worry — this is a very process, even for It’s upsetting that something that seems so simple ends up being so complex and , but remember: be patient, persistent, and do not accept “no” for Step 2: Analyze, Understand, and Fix the Issue Most billing issues that we encounter fall into 4 different buckets (described below). It’s important to understand which bucket you fall into (though it may be more than one) so that you take the right path to rectifying the (If you’re unclear that any of these 4 buckets apply to you, it’s likely you have a more complex Contact us directly to make an app

The International Development Finance Corporation (DFC), launched with bipartisan support in , mobilizes private investment to projects in emerging markets that support development, advance American foreign policy, and improve DFC provides tools like financing, political risk insurance, and support for emerging market private equity funds when sufficient commercial financing cannot be Projects supported by DFC build critical infrastructure and expand access to key services such as healthcare, technology, and small business All DFC projects adhere to high standards on the environment, human rights, and worker Is DFC part of the Government? DFC was established in through the passage of the BUILD, or Better Utilization of Investments Leading to Development, Act which strengthened and modernized American development The BUILD Act combined the capabilities of the Overseas Private Investment Corporation (OPIC) and the Development Credit Authority which had previously been housed in the Agency for International Development (USAID). Are DFC services taxpayer funded? DFC operates on a basis at no net cost to American Why is DFC important to the United States? DFC advances American foreign policy and American commercial The investments DFC mobilizes serve as stabilizing forces in developing countries around the world, including some of the world’s poorest countries and regions affected by Investment in these markets also helps American businesses gain footholds in many of the world’s How does DFC support development in emerging markets? Debt Financing , loans and guaranties of up to $500 million tenors as long as years for , commercial projects that are unable to raise sufficient corporate financing Political Risk Insurance Protection up to $500 million against losses resulting from currency inconvertibility, expropriation, regulatory risk, political violence, and breach of contract Investment Funds Support for emerging market private equity funds that invest in new and expanding emerging market businesses Technical Assistance Targeted technical assistance for potential projects Feasibility Studies Evaluation of viability, sustainability, or impact of potential projects Which projects are eligible for DFC support? All projects DFC supports must be based in countries where DFC is authorized to do business, meet DFC investment standards, and have a strong track record in the What types of projects does DFC support? DFC supports projects in a variety of industries from critical infrastructure to power generation, healthcare, agriculture, technology, and financial How is DFC different from the Overseas Private Investment Corporation? Key changes include: Equity Authority In addition to debt financing DFC has the ability to make equity investments, a tool widely used in development finance A Higher Investment Cap DFC has a total investment limit of $60 billion, more than double OPIC’s $29 billion investment cap Technical Assistance and Feasibility Studies DFC has new tools that will enable it t

A battery storage project combines familiar battery technologies, like those found in mobile electronics and electric vehicles, at scale to deliver and services to Batteries help to modernize the grid by providing energy on demand with projects designed to charge when electricity is cheap and discharge when it’s needed Not only do storage projects add economic value to the communities they serve, they also support a future with more renewable energy by helping to manage unpredictable wind and solar Why host a battery storage project on your land? A lease agreement with Delorean offers landowners revenue from to years with relatively little impact on your Projects can provide tax revenues to your community while also reducing local electricity At the end of the lease, Delorean pledges to return the associated land to its original state, ensuring continued land value for you and your How long does it take to develop a battery storage project? Due to the nature of development, each battery storage project may have a very different timeline to ensure we are exceeding local, state and federal If you have questions about the timeline of a project near you, please reach out to the Delorean team for more What does a battery storage project look like? Each battery storage project bundles battery technologies and integrates them into the surrounding landscape utilizing responsible development The visual aesthetics of our projects are carefully managed, and the project itself will have limited, if any, visibility from its land For each project site, Delorean prioritizes existing vegetation to create a visually appealing vegetative buffer around the In the instance the surrounding landscape does not offer vegetation, we commit to providing a buffer that fits the input of the Projects have a compact footprint, typically spanning less than one (1) acre of Does battery storage support a cleaner environment? Battery storage facilitates larger amounts of renewable wind and solar power at a time when states and the federal government are adopting more aggressive clean energy Projects are minimally invasive occupying a small land footprint and have little to no environmental impact (no water use, no emissions). How does Delorean ensure safety? A large body of codes and standards exist that support the safe design, operations, and decommissioning of energy storage systems, along with common protocols for hazard reduction, mitigation and Proper preparation, design, and prevention are considered at the early stages of project planning and coordination with national, state and local agencies ensure the safety of our battery storage Think your land is a good fit? We appreciate your interest in becoming a Delorean landowner! MOCA Cards for People FAQs | MOCA Financial Skip to content Personal I Want To… MOCA Cards For People MocaMoney Frequently Asked Questions Business I Want To… MOCA Cards for Business MocaMoney Frequently Asked Questions Rewards Contact Frequently Asked Questions for People General Sending and Receiving Money Types of MOCA Cards for Consumers Information about PINS Rewards Ways to use my MOCA Card Card Lost or Stolen Get Help Cancel Card General Q: What is a MOCA Card? A: MOCA Cards are a family of debit, prepaid, and gift cards powered by Visa® and issued under the MOCA You can use any MOCA Card anywhere Visa is MOCA Cards are “smart” cards and let you do things that most debit cards won’t. Q: How is my MOCA Card different? A: MOCA Cards provide more security, more control, and MOCA Prime accounts offer unlimited Here are a few of the things you can do with a MOCA card that makes it different: Instantly send money to anyone, anywhere at any time in using just their email address—and it’s free! Monitor your transactions in including a card on off as many virtual or physical reloadable MOCA Cash Debit Cards to yourself as you like reloadable MOCA Sentinel Debit Cards to your children and others and monitor the transactions on those cards in as well as set controls on when, where, and how those cards can be Attach pictures of receipts, warranties or other documents to any Set advanced controls such as spending limits by amount, time of day, day of week, category of merchant, and restrict use based on distance from your home zip Lock a card down to a single merchant for online Earn unlimited rewards with a MOCA Prime account! Q: How can I get a MOCA Prime Card? A: Easy, but you need a checking account at a participating Community Bank or Credit If you have one, you can upgrade to a Free MOCA Prime account and be carrying a MOCA Prime Card in no Give your local bank or credit union a call or visit their website to see if they offer MOCA Prime accounts! Q: Can I get a MOCA Card if I don’t have a MOCA Prime account? A: Generally, the only way to get a MOCA Card without a MOCA Prime account is if someone gives you a MOCA Card or someone sends you money through You can’t go to a participating Bank or Credit Union and buy a MOCA Cash Debit Card, for instance, although some participating Banks or Credit Unions may allow you to purchase a MOCA Gift Q: Are there any fees or other charges associated with my MOCA Card? A: None, except for a $5 fee for additional plastic Q: Is the MOCA Card a credit card? A: MOCA Cards are not credit The money you spend on a MOCA Card must either be in your MOCA Prime account or have been added to a MOCA Cash Debit Card or MOCA Sentinel Debit Q: Who is MOCA? A: MOCA is an Austin, FinTech company that is certified by VISA and distributes its MOCA Smart Card Technology through community financial Q: Where can I get the MOCA Mobile app? A: You can download MOCA Mobile from the App Store (iOS) or Google Play (Android). Q: How much does the MOCA Mobile app cost? A: Nothing, nada, It’s Q: Is my MOCA Prime account FDIC or NCUA insured? A: Of course! All MOCA Prime accounts carry $250,000 insurance protection from the FDIC (banks) or NCUA (credit unions). For more info, check out for cards issued by banks or for cards issued by credit Q: What is the purpose of my address in my MOCA User Profile? A: The address in your MOCA User Profile is used (1) to verify authorize transactions, and (2) as the address of record for any or Card notices, such as a MOCA Sentinel Debit or MOCA Cash Any notices sent regarding a or Card will be sent to the address in your MOCA User Any notices sent regarding your Prime or Premier accounts, including the cards, will be sent to the address currently on file with your financial Sending and Receiving Money Q: How do I send money to someone? A: Just use MocaMoney on MOCA Mobile or our MOCA desktop All you need is a MOCA Prime account and the recipient’s email Access the “Send Money” functionality, choose or add your recipient, and tell MOCA how much money to It’s that Q: Can I send money to someone who doesn’t have a social security number? A: Yes, but they can only take the money on a MOCA Gift Card, which is limited to a value of $1,000 and can be used at any merchant that accepts Visa in stores or Gift cards have a limit of $1,000 and may not be used to obtain Q: How do I claim money that someone sent me? A: Well, that depends on whether you currently have a MOCA Card or If you have a MOCA Prime account, any money sent to you through MocaMoney will be automatically deposited in your MOCA Prime If you don’t have a MOCA Prime account, but you have a reloadable MOCA Cash Debit Card or MOCA Sentinel Debit Card, the money will automatically be added to your MOCA Card If you are totally new to MOCA, you will receive an email with instructions on how to claim your money and you can claim it on a virtual or physical MOCA Gift Card or a virtual or physical MOCA Cash Debit Types

the fact that the superstars we all look up to on TV are more than just Many of them give back to the community, enjoy hobbies outside of sports, and are involved in the business Calvert Clark is certainly an example of a young superstar who is far more than just the ranked Class of baseball player in the His ability to lead by example on the field is only part of what makes him such a unique prospect at a young At home, he likes to relax through playing the piano with his best song being “Say You Won’t Let Go” by James Outside of playing the piano, his favorite artist is Alicia Keys and he enjoys watching the TV show “13 Reasons Why” as it is a great reminder to treat all people with respect because you never know what somebody is going through in His favorite class at Charlotte Christian School is Old Testament as he finds comfort in studying the word of God and often refers to Joshua 1:9 “Be strong and courageous do not be frightened or dismayed, for the Lord your God is with you wherever you ” Calvert’s grandfather introduced him to baseball on the front steps of their home in Queens, New They would play catch together routinely allowing Calvert to develop a deep passion for the game at a young Despite growing up experiencing an incredible amount of success on the field, Calvert still looks back on the time he was able to spend playing catch with his grandfather as his some of his favorite memories in As a member of the highly scouted Team Elite Prime, some of Calvert’s best moments on the field have come over the Most notably in a WWBA elimination game when he went with a go ahead home run late in the Calvert recalls the count being when he took a juicy fastball high and inside making it , “I stepped out thinking he would go to his changeup because I knew he had a good one, but he repeated with a high fastball and this time I got the barrel out in front and hit it over the left field fence about When I came to home plate with my teammates waiting for me I was the happiest grader I could ” There’s no doubt that Calvert woke up and crushed his lucky breakfast of a bagel, scrambled eggs and bacon with apple juice that morning like he does before every summer baseball While Calvert’s favorite player may be New York Yankee Aaron Hicks, his style of play is most similar to that of Matt Both outfielders who have powerful, high End Game — We Make Games End Game Our Story Games End Game x Our Next Chapter Our Story Yang Liu · Yang Liu · February , Today, I’m excited to finally announce End Game’s $3M seed round! We are incredibly lucky to have such great friends support us on our This includes Jay Chi, Ryann Lai, and rest of the team at Makers Fund Jaakko Harlas and the Supercell team Kevin Lin from Twitch Hubert Thieblot — previously of Curse — now also at Twitch David Helgason from Unity Danny Epstien and Alexandre Cohen at Main Street Advisors and Scooter Braun of SB Projects (Ariana Grande, Justin Bieber, J Balvin). The Past When we first started creating games — just me, Luke, and Jeremiah (for without whom, not much of this would be possible) in our rooms at home, we never expected it to grow into anything, especially not into Before our first game, , we had no experience making games at We had no idea what we were doing – and that hasn’t really changed, That’s what makes our investor’s trust in us so special, and why we’re so grateful that they want to join us on our journey towards creating more memorable experiences for Most importantly, we feel the most gratitude towards every single person that has stopped by and played our games in the past – whether you’ve put 1,000+ hours into or you just simply swung by to say hi on . There’s been over ,000,000 million of you that have played Zombs, Spinz and Zombs Royale from over countries – that’s almost all the countries! So, thank you to everyone, especially our very passionate community that I know is eagerly waiting for updates and our next games! In , Zombs Royale was launched and we became one of the Top Most Googled Games ! It was at this point that we said to ourselves, “Hey, maybe we can do something bigger,” while still not understanding what we were doing It has been an incredibly fun and fulfilling journey making games that bring joy to our players’ We see all the fan art, all the videos, and all the suggestions that our players To be able to make an experience that people dream about and want to spend more time in is a dream come There’s no better job than to continue serving people around the world with delightful experiences through We cannot wait to bring even more new experiences to you Looking Forward In terms of what this means for the company — we will be scaling our We’ve had some of the most amazing team members join us in the past year, and we’ve grown so much We are so excited to show you guys what we have been up We will continue to focus on what we believe is a huge frontier for It’s something that has been around for decades, but we feel still has so much This is simply – , multiplayer Growing up around games, there has been nothing that can replicate the feeling of meeting someone in a video game and simply “hanging out” in the comfort of your own This was stigmatized as a “nerdy” but not anymore! By , multiplayer games – we mean the instinctively social core you see in certain games this ranges from games that are as basic as and , to , highly games such as Along with this multiplayer core, we will be continuing our belief in a ubiquitous gaming We accidentally stumbled on making Zombs Royale (it was intended to be web only until our players asked for and then PC!). We truly believe that platform and hardware shouldn’t limit access to any form of social Just as how anyone should be able to go to a coffee shop, a zoo, or a theme With that said, we hope to be making our games available on as many platforms and hardware as As for what you guys can expect from us next – we are launching a game titled Fate Arena soon! It will be a Strategic Online Battle Arena game, more commonly known as an “auto-battler,” or “autochess.” It is our twist on the incredibly fun genre that you may have seen We hope to create a social, casual and fun experience for everyone new and experienced with the The page is now live at ! Here are some screenshots: But that’s not all! In addition to Fate Arena, our wonderful teams have been working on many other games that we hope to share as soon as we We are super excited about all of them, and hope that you guys will get to see them soon! Thank you again to everyone who has been alongside us throughout our We are incredibly grateful for all the friends, family and players that support We hope to make amazing games for you all! Why did you build Tellor? What is an oracle? What is “The Oracle Problem?” How does Tellor solve this problem? How do you differ from the competition? Tellor is a decentralized Oracle for bringing high value data onto The system utilizes a network of staked miners that compete to solve a PoW challenge to submit the official value for requested Tokens are mined with every successful Tellor data point and the company takes a % dev share to support the development of the Why did you build Tellor? We originally set out to build Tellor because our previous startup, Daxia (a derivatives protocol on Ethereum) needed an Daxia created tokens that would represent the short or long side of crypto pricing pairs, BTC USD for We relied on a centralized oracle to provide the price data points to settle the We knew this didn’t fit with our ambitions to be a fully decentralized protocol and so we set out to find a decentralized oracle that would fit our That solution didn’t So we set out to build it What is an oracle? An oracle provides data and submits this information to a blockchain to be used by smart Typically this is a data feed provided by a third party What is "The Oracle Problem?" Since smart contracts on Ethereum are fully and any information or access to data is restricted, certain types of smart contracts are reliant on an outside provider (an oracle) of data The problem is that you now have a decentralized smart contract with a centralized key point of The issue with this is obvious to anyone who values How does Tellor solve this problem? Tellor set out to solve the oracle problem in a specific context: a lack of secure and decentralized price feeds for DeFi Tellor aims to enable the growth of the DeFi industry by providing a secure source of for high quality pricing The Tellor Oracle is an data bank where miners compete to add the data To create a properly incentivized system Tellor mints a native token, “Tributes.” Parties pay Tellor Tributes to submit a request for data to the Based upon the reward assigned to each request, the Oracle selects the best funded query every ten minutes to create a challenge for miners to Each query collects specific data (e.g. ETH USD or BTC USD prices) and makes it available has proven to be the gold standard for crypto economic consensus mechanisms and Tellor utilizes it within a hybrid model to secure the In addition to the security provided by the PoW process, we have added an additional layer of security through the deposit of Tributes which miners are required to stake before they are allowed to mine and risk losing their stake if their submitted values are successfully How do you differ from the competition? Our competitors have different philosophical views when it comes to Similar to how Ethereum, EOS, and Hyperledger all have different models when it comes to who ultimately secures their protocol, Tellor aims to be a system that is truly censorship resistant and transparent in its We’ve built a system that ensures accuracy and liveness all while being completely open for anyone to become a data reporter or validator and take part in the This approach contrasts starkly from competition who use centralized whitelisting, reputation of known parties, or other trusted architectures in their In addition to the pure tech side, token distribution of your governance protocol We did no ICO, no premine, and have worked tirelessly to build an active community of philosophically aligned individuals with a highly distributed token What is the purpose of your token, Tellor Tributes? Repayments are suspended when earning less than the Floor, and total payments will never exceed the ISAs are NOT The money advanced is not a It is an investment in the student’s future earning There is no accruing interest, no principal balance, and no penalty if the amount ultimately repaid is less than the amount Aligned Incentives ISAs help reduce financial barriers to education and align incentives between school, student and Inquire About Partnership Opportunities ISA Key Terms Funded Amount The amount funded on the student’s behalf Income Share The percentage of monthly income repaid after graduation (subject to the Floor and Cap) Annual Income The student’s income (i.e., Line 1 of IRS Form ) Monthly Payment The dollar amount repaid by the student on a monthly basis Minimum Threshold The “Floor”. Repayment Obligations are suspended when Annual Income is less than the Floor Payment Cap The “Ceiling”. ISA automatically terminates once aggregate repayments reach the Required Payments The number of required Monthly Payments (subject to the Floor, but never to exceed the Payment Window) Payment Window The outer limit on obligations ISA Program Benefits Increase Access & Opportunity Democratize access to education by eliminating barriers Eliminate Financial Risk ISA tuition options remove the risk associated with pursuing continued education Aligned Interests School is incentivized to ensure graduates obtain the best jobs possible Signal Value Enhance school reputation by joining a prominent group of institutions offering ISAs Student Recruitment & Retention ISAs are proven to attract and help keep students in school ISAs Provide Better Diversification Than Image credit: Manhattan Institute Financing multiple ISAs can reduce losses relative to traditional loans, as losses from Under a traditional loan, students may face difficulty replaying their To compensate, lender must demand higher interest rates from all With an ISA, repayments from are reduced or waived (making default less likely), while rep

Menu Home Meet the Developer: Sungchul Park September 3, September 4, ~ Ocean Drive Studio For today’s blog, please meet Sungchul Park, CTO for the game projects at Ocean Drive Studio . Quick Intro Name: Sungchul Park Your Role: Leader of tech Tech group is in charge of creating root tech systems and structures related to developing graphics, game systems, game server network, and Basically tech group takes role of realizing what creative group envisions! and during the process we create infrastructure for the all of our future game What Else? : I have a lovely wife, two kids and two cats! My main role for the family is making sure our home is clean and safe! Also, I love travelling… and current Covid pandemic is giving me hard time… can’t wait to travel with my family once the pandemic gets British Short Hair and Scottish Fold (without folded ears!) Can’t forget the trip to Honolulu! Games as a Gamer Favorite Games: One of my all time favorite is To the Moon by Freebird Games . To the Moon is not only fun, but also the game which provides me with feeling of comfort, joy and I learned game can be a form of art, and game can provide many different values by playing this This is why I call To the Moon as my all time favorite game although this game has relatively short playing My all time favorite FINDING PARADISE Of course, another Sigmund Series Finding Paradise is another game that I have to When I first played the game, I had to agree that it is very hard to find the sequel better than the until I have reached the ending of the It was more touching than To the Moon ! I can’t wait to play Imposter Factory which is due end of the Favorite Game Studios: My favorite game studio is Blizzard Entertainment . There are exceptions, but most of their games provides the best possible gaming experience within the Fans always wait for the new titles or sequels, and Blizzard always try to satisfy community’s Their craftsmanship making the game, and always trying to communicate with the community is something I admire and expect Ocean Drive to What have you been playing lately?: Assetto Corsa is the game I have been playing with I have always loved cars, and after watching F1: Drive to Survive I couldn’t stop playing this Recently, I have been playing this game with my colleagues at the studio, changing tracks every week, competing the best lap Every time I watch YouTube video of real driving on the track I have been playing on the game, I feel amazed how accurate and realistic the game ASSETO CORSA – The Set Up in the Office I have been also playing Animal Crossing with my kids! My 8 daughter and 4 son love playing this I am limiting game time to mins only on My kids have been always waiting for the weekend to come only for this My kids have been loving Mario Kart, Mario Party, Kirby Star Allies and now Animal Now, I can say I am a huge fan of both Kirby (enjoyed different types of fusion combinations) and Animal Crossing (what makes sandbox game so fun!)! Last time, my wife has told me to stop making excuse of kids playing these games! The Island my family has been working together – Easter decoration is not my taste though! This was a critical moment in my life, where I started to think maybe I can become a game Key Philosophy: Key word for the game development for me is “Culture”. Most of the games I have played passionately always had elements of culture, meaning either online or offline, or sometimes both online and offline, I always formed community sharing the game experience with As other art does, game becomes something valuable in our lives when it becomes culture and connects It applies for the game development When entire game development process involves many different people with different taste and expertise, the culture within the development team gets shared with the I always think the game developed by a team without culture cannot be attractive, and at Ocean Drive, one of our main focus is having a unique and attractive culture which can influence our game projects! My Past Projects: During my early gaming career at Nexon, I worked on Elancia, Asgard, Elemental Saga , and Crazy Arcade B&B . Approach - Triplet Therapeutics Home About Approach Patients News Join Us Contact APPROACH Preventing Repeat Expansion Disorders at Their Source More than known genetic diseases are associated with DNA Many of these diseases, collectively known as repeat expansion disorders, are caused by nucleotide repeats that occur in various genes throughout the body and expand over Examples of repeat expansion disorders include Huntington’s disease, myotonic dystrophy and various spinocerebellar ​ Patients with repeat expansion disorders are born with a certain number of repeats in their Throughout the patient’s life, the repeats expand and increase in number, which is what drives the A growing body of evidence points to one central pathway underlying repeat expansion disorders: the DNA damage response (DDR) Modifying this pathway therefore holds promise to treat a wide array of repeat expansion disorders at their The Science Behind Repeat Expansion Disorders ​A robust body of human genetic evidence, including association studies and analysis of human single variants, has identified certain proteins within the DDR pathway that drive repeat Our approach selectively knocks down the RNA that encodes those proteins while leaving the underlying DNA repair mechanism 1 Repeat expansion disorders are genetic disorders associated with expanded DNA nucleotide Genetic data from thousands of patients has revealed that the DNA damage response pathway (DDR) drives DNA repeat expansion, and that number of DNA repeats is associated with disease onset and More than of these disorders have been identified, most of which are severe with limited treatment 2 DNA damage response (DDR) proteins drive repeat DDR proteins are important cellular gatekeepers however, when they encounter certain long DNA repeat hairpins, DDR proteins can drive repeat Expanded DNA repeats are associated with disease onset and progression across multiple repeat expansion 3 Triplet is targeting specific DDR proteins with ASOs and siRNAs to stop repeat Triplet is developing antisense oligonucleotides and small interfering RNAs to partially knock down the expression of the DDR proteins involved in repeat Partial knockdown of these proteins prevents malfunction while preserving essential DNA surveillance and repair 4 Triplet s approach is designed to halt disease onset and progression by precisely reducing activity of select DDR The approach is applicable across a wide range of diseases, including Huntington s disease, myotonic dystrophy and select spinocerebellar ​Our approach is to precisely reduce the expression of select DDR genes leveraging two therapeutic modalities: antisense oligonucleotides (ASOs) and small interfering RNAs (siRNAs). These approaches are tailored to inactivate only the elements of the DDR pathway that drive expansion, while leaving intact DNA repair Triplet’s development candidates operate upstream of today’s leading Current approaches achieve only partial reduction in levels of toxic RNA or pr
